gomodel:SYNGO_5177  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Figure 2b-h: hippocampal immunostaining showed partial co-localization of endogenous Slc4a8 with presynaptic proteins synaptophysin (SYP), vGlut1 and vGlut2. Overlap with GAD67 as a marker of GABAergic presynapses was marginal. No co-localization was observed for postsynaptic marker PSD95 (DLG4) and dendritic marker MAP2.\n\nFigure 2i: in biochemical fractions from mouse brain lysate, Slc4a8 was detected in synaptosomes and synaptic membrane fractions but not in PSD. Staining was absent in Slc4a8-knockout control mice.\n\nFigure 2j-l: \"Immunogold labeling of freeze-fractured WT and KO synaptosome preparations proved that the Slc4a8 signal was specific (Fig. 2J,K) and that Slc4a8 and Syntaxin-a well established presynaptic protein (Okada et al., 1995)-localized to the same compartment in WT preparations (Fig. 2L)\".\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.\n\nAuthors discussed on non-synaptic localization:\n\"Slc4a8 was detected in protein lysates of mixed neuron/glia cell cultures, but not of cultured glia cells (Fig. 1E). Accordingly, no overlap of Slc4a8 was noted with the astrocyte marker GFAP or the oligodendrocyte marker CNPase in immunostainings of brain sections (data not shown). The somata of Slc4a8-stained neurons were labeled variably, some displaying a clear plasma membrane-bound signal and some a more intracellular vesicular staining (see also close-up from pyramidal cell layer, Fig. 2H). Slc4a8 did not colocalize with the dendritic marker MAP2 (Fig. 2F). Costaining with the axonal marker NF68 revealed that Slc4a8 localized to axons rather than dendrites (data not shown).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"For immunohistochemistry, brains of 6- to 8-week-old wild-type (WT) and KO mice were ...\"\n\nantibody:\npolyclonal rabbit Slc4a8 antibody (Leviel et al., 2010). PMID:20389022\nFigure 1: validation of the Slc4a8 antibody using westernblot of wildtype and knockout mouse brains." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5177" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

